Audio/Video Affiliates Inc said ithas authorized the purchase of up to 2.5 mln shares of itscommon stock, in market transactions, from time to time.    The company said the purchases were authorized because itbelieves the market price of the stock is less than itsunderlying value. Audio/Video said general funds of the companywill be used to purchase the shares, and all shares will beheld in the company's treasury, for possible future use. Reuter&#3;